    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: 
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: If we were working in 2.5D or 3D, we would need to cast this
          ray out the camera, and find a point in the world where it hits. Instead,
          because we are working in 2D, and every object we have made so far has
          been as Z position of 0, we can calculate the world space point that the
          player clicked by slightly adjusting the ray's origin.
      m_PollItems: []
      m_PollCorrectItemIndexes: 00000000
      m_Tutorial: {fileID: 0}
      m_Image: {fileID: 0}
      disableImagePopup: 0
      m_Video: {fileID: 0}
