    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: 
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "The origin of the array is the world space position on the
          surface of the camera (i.e. the X and Y positions are in the same space
          as the objects in the world). The only problem with this origin is that
          our camera is placed at position -10 on the Z axis (if it were placed at
          z=0, nothing would render). All the code above is doing is setting the
          z axis value of the origin to 0, so that it matches the positions of the
          other objects in the game.\r\nRun the game and examine the console output,
          noting how screen space is being converted into world space. Your numbers
          may be different to mine, depending on your screen resolution and camera
          position. \r\n"
      m_PollItems: []
